## Research Summary

### 1. Linear Design Patterns (Aesthetic Reference)
**Source**: [Linear Redesign Blog](https://linear.app/now/how-we-redesigned-the-linear-ui), [LogRocket Analysis](https://blog.logrocket.com/ux-design/linear-design/)

**What we adopt from Linear:**
- Dark mode as default (#0D0D0D base, not pure black)
- LCH color space for perceptually uniform themes
- Three-variable theme: base color, accent color, contrast
- Minimalist, focused interface
- Generous whitespace and subtle borders
- Typography-first hierarchy
- Smooth micro-interactions

**What we DON'T adopt (different domain):**
- Sprint-based project views → We use mileage-based scheduling
- Issue tracking patterns → We use maintenance task patterns
- Short-term roadmaps → We need 12-year strategic views

### 2. Scheduling Software Patterns (Domain Reference)
**Sources**:
- [DHTMLX Gantt Fleet Scheduling](https://xbsoftware.com/blog/fleet-management-software-dhtmlx-gantt)
- [ULTRAMAIN Maintenance Scheduling](https://www.aircraftit.com/vendors/ultramain-systems/maintenance-scheduling/)
- [Instagantt Fleet Management](https://www.instagantt.com/project-templates/fleet-management-timeline)

**Key patterns to adopt:**
- Gantt chart timeline visualization
- Drag-and-drop rescheduling
- Dark theme support (DHTMLX v9.0)
- Real-time conflict detection
- Resource allocation visualization
- Dependency lines between tasks

### 3. Railway Maintenance Software (Industry Reference)
**Sources**:
- [Railnova Railfleet](https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/)
- [ZEDAS Asset](https://www.zedas.com/en/zedas-solution-logistics-solution-and-asset-management/zedasasset-asset-management/)
- [Boom Rail Solutions](https://rail.boomsoftware.com/en/)

**Key patterns:**
- Fleet overview dashboard
- Train status indicators (operational/maintenance/out-of-service)
- Mileage-based preventive maintenance scheduling
- Maintenance intervention planning
- ECM (Entity in Charge of Maintenance) compliance

### 4. What-If Scenario Patterns (Primary Feature)
**Sources**:
- [Epicflow What-If Analysis](https://www.epicflow.com/features/what-if/)
- [Triskell Scenario Planning](https://triskellsoftware.com/triskell-platform-key-features/scenario-analysis/)
- [Cube Scenario Modeling](https://www.cubesoftware.com/scenario-what-if-analysis)

**Key patterns to adopt:**
- Simulation mode toggle (Live vs Sandbox)
- Visual differentiation for scenarios (distinct color accent)
- Delta metrics panel (before/after comparison)
- Scenario save/load/compare functionality
- Undo/redo in simulation mode
- Apply scenario to baseline action

### 5. deck.gl Visualization Patterns
**Source**: [deck.gl Showcase](https://deck.gl/showcase)

**Working image URLs from deck.gl:**
- `https://deck.gl/images/showcase/kepler-gl.jpg` - Kepler.gl
- `https://deck.gl/images/showcase/flowmap.jpg` - Flowmap.blue
- `https://deck.gl/images/showcase/sanddance.jpg` - SandDance
