## Document Structure

### Part 1: Vision & Philosophy
- Executive summary solving RFQ pain points
- Design philosophy (Linear mood + Domain expertise)
- Clear attribution table (what comes from where)

### Part 2: Moodboard
- **Linear-inspired**: App screenshots from Mobbin/Linear blog
- **Scheduling-inspired**: DHTMLX Gantt, Instagantt examples
- **Railway-inspired**: Railfleet dashboard references
- **Visualization-inspired**: deck.gl showcase (Kepler.gl, Flowmap, SandDance)
- All images with working `<img>` tags

### Part 3: RFQ Pain Points → Solutions Matrix
- All 9 pain points from RFQ
- Specific UI solutions for each
- Screen/component mapping

### Part 4: Design System
- Color palette (dark mode, semantic colors, sandbox accent)
- Typography (Inter, JetBrains Mono)
- Spacing, borders, radius tokens
- Component styling guidelines

### Part 5: Screen Specifications

#### 5.1 Application Shell
- Navbar with mode toggle
- Sidebar (fleet list)
- Main canvas area
- Status bar

#### 5.2 Planning View (Primary)
- Semantic zoom levels (MACRO/MESO/MICRO)
- Timeline header with adaptive granularity
- Task visualization at each zoom level
- Minimap component

#### 5.3 Sandbox Mode (PRIMARY FEATURE)
- Mode toggle UI (LIVE ↔ SANDBOX)
- Visual differentiation (violet accent)
- Sandbox panel with delta metrics
- Editable interactions (drag, resize, create, delete)
- Compare view (baseline vs scenario)
- Saved scenarios management

### Part 6: Components Specification
- TaskBlock (with states: normal, hover, selected, conflict, modified)
- KPICard
- AlertBanner
- Minimap
- ModeToggle
- TrainRow (sidebar)

### Part 7: Data Structures
- Train entity
- Task entity
- Scenario entity (for what-if)
- Mock data generation config

### Part 8: Interactions & Gestures
- Canvas navigation (pan, zoom, pinch)
- Task interactions (hover, select, drag, resize)
- Keyboard shortcuts

### Part 9: Implementation Notes
- Stack: Astro.js + deck.gl + XState + Tailwind
- Performance targets
- File structure proposal

